. The Lore Rationale
Step Store → Kinetic Mapping Dynamo: You aren't buying upgrades with a pedometer. The ship in orbit is blind due to atmospheric interference. It needs your exo-suit to physically walk the terrain to generate localized topographical data. By sending the ship "Steps" (Kinetic Data), you map the planet for it. In exchange, its orbital fabricators beam down upgrades or unlock new atmospheric teleport zones for you.
Tracks → Mag-Lev Conduits: Laying down dirt tracks doesn't make sense. Instead, you are expending kinetic data to micro-fabricate Phase-Alloy Conduits onto the ground. When your suit steps onto these, it magnetically repels them—essentially turning you into a frictionless Mag-Lev train across the terrain.
